can't really liquefy it easily to coat Wolvy's

00:01:35.670 --> 00:01:38.850
bones wihtout
also liquefying his skin.

00:01:38.850 --> 00:01:43.690
There are strong, tough nanomaterials - alloys
and other specially cultivated substances.

00:01:43.690 --> 00:01:44.740
For example,

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:46.920
wurtzite boron nitrate

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:49.299
a super strong crystalline substance with
a hugh melting point,

00:01:49.299 --> 00:01:51.960
but unfortunately, it's an irritant.

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:56.470
So if Logan deployed his claws, he'd cause
cell damage to the eyes and respiratory systems

00:01:56.470 --> 00:01:58.060
to anyone in
the vicinity.

00:01:58.060 --> 00:01:59.060
DAMN IT!

00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:02.640
I'm thinking the best bet would probably be
aggregated diamond nano-rods.

00:02:02.640 --> 00:02:05.510
If you take graphene and you roll it into
a tube and then press

00:02:05.510 --> 00:02:06.780
it together,

00:02:06.780 --> 00:02:09.749
it's super strong, it has a high melting
point - it's actually stronger than

00:02:09.749 --> 00:02:11.000
diamonds - and it wouldn't

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.799
kill anyone by being exposed to air.

00:02:13.799 --> 00:02:15.239
Which is a plus.

00:02:15.239 --> 00:02:18.170
In the movies, Wolverine has adamantium
injected

00:02:18.170 --> 00:02:20.359
into his body so it could coat his bones.

00:02:20.359 --> 00:02:22.260
And
thanks to its healing factor he survives

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:23.840
where others would have not.

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:24.840
That's heavy doc.

